message.content:
"My-ee-es," he lowered his eyes and kissed her on the mouth an act of devotion he didn't over-indulge.

"What about it, my sweet?" "Well," she laughed suddenly in an upsurging of relief, "that stupid Gullins boy thought he saw you at the load of trouble. With a blonde too. Imagine!" Nigel was frowning. He looked distinguished when he frowned; boyishly handsome at other times.
